------------ FEMS 

## BACKEND-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
------ .env 
-> storage for system specific configs as well as secrets

------ app.js
-> "conducts/glues" the entire application together
-> imports
-> it parses the req body if it is of content-type: application/json and populates the req.body with it
-> sets up dbconnection
-> routes to authentication part and users part
-> tells the server to listen to requests

------ utils
--- admin-creation.js
-> A utility async function to create the admin if not already present in DB
-> called in app.js (when starting the server)

------ routes
--- auth.routes.js
-> takes care of routing for authentication
--- user.routes.js
-> takes care of routing for home page + users (getting users, POSTing (saving in DB) users)

------ config
--- db.js
-> defines the async function to connect to the database: tries to connect, else kills the backend on failure

------ controllers
-> controllers contain all the code as functions which take the request from the user and accordinly manipulate data from the database to satisfy the request as a response
--- admin.controller.js
-> creates organizer given field values
--- auth.controller.js
-> contains the logic for a new participant signup and a login for organizer and participant. also contains helper function make make a JWT out of input fields
--- user.controller.js
-> contains the logic for how to save a user to and how to get users, and how to get organizers from DB
------ middleware
--- auth.middleware.js
-> Intercepts requests and determines whether to let them pass through or not (token-based [JWT])
-> It follows a passing the baton kind of mechanism to affirm (Single Responsibility Principle). It is implemented using next()

------ models
--- organizer.js
--- participant.js
--- user.js
the base schema; utilized polymorphism (schema inheritance) via a mongoose mehthod called discriminator. it 
allows me to store users of all type in a single mongodb collection

------ docs
--- architecture
--- devlogs

------ node_modules

------ package-lock.json

------ package.json

## FRONTEND ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

